# Project Rules (.cursorrules)

The project root **.cursorrules** file is the source of truth for fundamental behavior and agent workflow. Always follow it.

## Key points (see .cursorrules for full text)

1. **Fundamental behavior** - Follow all project and cursor rules; read prompts fully; move iteratively; consult .cursor/plans and AGENTIC_WORKFLOW when stuck; ask when uncertain; do not update .cursorrules or human docs without approval.
2. **Agentic workflow** - Work is orchestrated by @planner and executed by agents (@config, @taskfile, @code-reviewer). No ad-hoc multi-file changes; explicit delegation and hand-offs.
3. **Plan naming** - `.cursor/plans/YYYY-MM-DD_<username>_<slug>.plan.md`.
4. **Dotfiles layout** - Config under etc/, nvim/, wezterm/, hammerspoon/, yazi/, tmux/, tasks/, scripts/; respect symlink layout.
5. **Security** - Timeouts for blocking ops; no sudo without approval; no destructive edits without confirmation.
6. **Pre-commit** - Run task precommit (or pre-commit-run skill) before commit / finish-branch.

When any rule in .cursor/ conflicts with .cursorrules, .cursorrules takes precedence for fundamental behavior and workflow. For task-specific details (e.g. plan format, debug phases), .cursor/rules/*.mdc apply.
